import React, { Component } from 'react'; import { Typography } from '@material-ui/core'; import PicOfMe from '../../pic_of_me.jpg'; import './home.css'; class Home extends Component { render() { return (
Hi, I'm Natalie. This is a simple React application to showcase that I, in fact, am capable of developing a web application. I decided that aesthetically I should do something that amuses me, so the site is rubber duck themed. Maybe it will help me figure out my issues. (If you're not a programmer, rubber ducking is a method for talking yourself through a programming problem) I graduated from Cal Poly SLO in March of 2019 with my Bachelors in Computer Science. While I never took a web class at school, I have a smidge over 2 years of professional experience with it. I have enjoyed working with modern frameworks such as React, Angular, and Backbone, and have also had the slightly lesser pleasure of reconstructing some really ugly framework-less code. While I primarily consider myself a front end developer, I have continuously written back end components to retrieve and process data to accomodate my front end tasks (aka I am perfectly comfortable with PHP and MySQL too). I grew up in Washington, have been in California for the past 6 years, and am currently squatting in Minnesota until I find a job wherever that may be. And by "wherever" I mean Colorado, Oregon, Washington, Minnesota, or California, because I do have preferences. Here is a photo of me so you can put a face to the name: {/*

x

y

z

*/}
); } } export default Home;
